In this statement, the President expresses deep concern over the reports of violence in Bahrain, Libya, and Yemen. The United States condemns the use of violence by governments against peaceful protesters in these countries and anywhere else it may occur. The President extends condolences to the families and friends of those who have been killed during the demonstrations. The statement emphasizes that people have universal rights, including the right to peaceful assembly, regardless of their location. The United States urges the governments of Bahrain, Libya, and Yemen to exercise restraint in responding to peaceful protests and to respect the rights of their people.